metadata.notes: CBA reports June FY, NAB/ANZ/WBC report September FY, Macquarie reports March FY. All metrics on cash/continuing operations basis. Macquarie is a diversified financial group — NIM and CTI not directly comparable to pure retail banks. Dividend yields calculated using approximate share prices at reporting dates (CBA ~$115, NAB ~$32, ANZ ~$27, WBC ~$27, MQG ~$200).

banks.name: Commonwealth Bank of Australia
banks.notes: Cash NPAT from continuing operations. NIM of 2.08% up 9bps driven by higher earnings on capital and replicating portfolio hedges. Hired 2,000+ engineers in FY25, investment spend up $300m to $2.3bn. OpenAI partnership for AI integration.

banks.name: National Australia Bank
banks.notes: Cash earnings essentially flat YoY. NIM up 3bps to 1.74%, partly driven by Markets & Treasury. Revenue up 2.9%. Loan impairment charges rose 14% to $833m. Investment spending stepped up to $1.8bn. Pro-forma CET1 of 11.81% after MLC Life sale completion.

banks.name: ANZ Banking Group
banks.notes: Cash profit down 14% due to $1.1bn significant items: $585m restructuring charge, $271m ASIC settlement. Underlying cash profit ex significant items ~$6.9bn, flat YoY. Revenue up 7% to $22.2bn. Pro-forma CET1 of 12.26% after capital return. NIM of ~1.55% under pressure from mortgage competition and Suncorp Bank integration dilution.

banks.name: Westpac Banking Corporation
banks.notes: Net profit down ~2% but ahead of analyst expectations of ~$6.83bn. NIM of 1.94% (core NIM 1.81%), down just 1bp. Operating expenses up 9% to $11.9bn including $273m UNITE restructuring charge. Business lending +15%, institutional lending +17%. Sold $21.4bn RAMS mortgage portfolio. CET1 12.5% provides $3.1bn surplus above 11.25% target.

banks.name: Macquarie Group
banks.notes: Net profit up 5% to $3.715bn. ROE of 11.2% (2H25 annualised 12.5%). MAM net profit contribution up 33%. BFS up 11% driven by home loan and deposit growth. Total deposits up 20% to $177.7bn. $9.5bn capital surplus. 56 consecutive years of profitability. NIM estimated for BFS banking division — Macquarie does not report a single group NIM comparable to the Big 4.
